Melatos (1998) solves for exact transverse wave solutions and finds two circularly polarized waves, one subluminal wave in which the particles are magnetized in the radial magnetic field, and consequently do not oscillate in the wave field so that γ±≈γd, and one superluminal wave in which the particles are unmagnetized and oscillate with the wave field so that \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
